--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages git.

Git is a fast, scalable, distributed revision control system with an unusually
rich command set that provides both high-level operations and full access to
internals. The git role installs the core tools with minimal dependencies.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: git
       git_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: git
       git_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  git_state
    Specify predetermined 'git_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  git: >= 1.7
    RedHat, CentOS

  dev-vcs/git: >= 1.8
    Gentoo

